<Prose title="About" description="Benjamin Schneider — bio, background, and contact.">
  <p>
    Solution architect at <a href="https://vivenu.com">Vivenu</a> in Zurich, working on event ticketing infrastructure.
    Previously built and led engineering teams at TICKETINO, and helped organize HackZurich and Digital Festival Zurich
    for several years.
  </p>

  <p>
    I studied informatics at the University of Zurich (BSc). Outside work, I lead command support for a civil protection
    unit in the Pfannenstiel region, contribute to OpenStreetMap, and read too much about molecular biology,
    information design, and Central European history.
  </p>

  <p>
    The best way to reach me is by email: <a href="mailto:mail@benjaminschneider.ch">mail@benjaminschneider.ch</a>.<br />
    Also on <a href="https://twitter.com/bschne">Twitter</a>,
    <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/bschne.bsky.social">Bluesky</a>, and
    <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/schneiderbenjamin">LinkedIn</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Work history</h2>

  <dl class="work-list">
    <dt>Vivenu <span class="work-period">2023–present</span></dt>
    <dd>Solution architect. Ticketing infrastructure and enterprise integrations.</dd>

    <dt>HackZurich <span class="work-period">2018–2023</span></dt>
    <dd>
      Helped organize one of Europe's largest hackathons, bringing together 500–1,200
      participants annually.
    </dd>

    <dt>Digital Festival Zurich <span class="work-period">2018–2023</span></dt>
    <dd>
